para_trans: Government Decision Number: Yantrakh 2025 / Q. No.318 / Pr.
Verification of not exceeding the rate should be done by the Commissioner (Medical Education) as well as the respective Dean.

The technical specification of the equipment should be comprehensive, comprehensive, and consistent with which the equipment supplier WHI will receive three bids from at least three manufacturers / suppliers. Also, the procurement process should be carried out only after verifying that the technical specifications are not designed to benefit any particular company.

The Commissioner (Medical Education) and the Principal concerned shall ensure that the proposed equipment is not included in any proposal elsewhere / is not allowed to be purchased and that the equipment is required by the institution concerned.

While deciding on the purchase of machinery in this regard, it should be ensured that the expenditure does not exceed the provision of grant-in-aid sanctioned under the head of accounting provided for administrative approval.
It will be necessary to show the prices of the main equipment and their accessories as different.
The Central Vigilance Commission (CVC) guidelines should be followed strictly while executing the entire procurement process.

The State Level Procurement Committee shall comply with the provision in the above mentioned judgment, paragraph no. 3. 9. 2 of the Department of Industry, Power and Labour, dated 01.12.2016, titled "Price Estimation and Price Reasonability" in paragraph no. 3.9.2.9.

Go. Since the machinery is to be procured on turn key basis, the machinery should be procured by following the procedure laid down in the Government Decision No.IHN-2019 / Q.No.293 / PRACH-1, dated: 07.03.2019 of the Department.
